Withania somnifera

   [10920.jpg]
   Authority (L.) Dunal
   Family Magnoliopsida:Asteridae:Solanales:Solanaceae
   Synonyms Withania ashwagandha
   Common names Indian ginseng, poisonous gooseberry, winter cherry,
   ajagandha, asgand, kanaje, samm al ferakh, amukkirag, amangura,
   asvagandha, ashvagandha, asundha, aswagandha, bitterappelliefie,
   geneesbossie, vernietsiektebossie, ubuvimba, umaqhunsula
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 10920

   Notes
   DESCRIPTION: It is an erect, greyish, slightly hairy shrub with a smell
   akin to that of a sweaty horse. USE: The roots, leaves, and the seeds
   all have medicinal properties. GROWING PERIOD: Perennial. Flowering and
   fruiting: September to November, and then March to May. COMMON NAMES:
   Indian ginseng, poisonous gooseberry, winter cherry. FURTHER INF: Open
   places, disturbed areas etc. An undershrub in stony places. Found in
   drier parts of India. Native of Australia, India, Pakistan, Sri Lanka,
   East Asia and Africa.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
